Jan. 23, 1888
My dear Annie and Azary;
How do you do? We some what looked for you people Saturday night but decided ti was too cold. I write this early in the week so that you can get some one to lead your young People's meeting next Sunday. The Father has a birthday next Sabbath and it is necessary that as many of the children as possible shall be present. Is your butter gone? I have a cunning little dish ready for you. We have not heard a word from any of you. I have so many letters to write that each must be short. You must have no excuse. You can change with some one. lovingly Mother.
